    "description": "Care Ratings Capital India is actively seeking a talented and motivated Credit Analyst to join our dynamic team in Varanasi. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Care Ratings Capital India:\nCare Ratings Capital India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Care Ratings Capital India!",
